WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.139 --> 00:00:02.726
<i>Previously on</i> Will Trent...

2
00:00:02.864 --> 00:00:05.798
Unfortunately. this dark area
right next to it is a tumor.

3
00:00:05.936 --> 00:00:08.716
-What should I do?
-Well. get it out as soon as possible.

4
00:00:08.801 --> 00:00:10.389
Faith? I need...

5
00:00:10.527 --> 00:00:12.736
Hey. Okay. I'm here. I'm here.

6
00:00:12.874 --> 00:00:14.324
<i>Sending an ambulance now.</i>

7
00:00:17.189 --> 00:00:18.742
<i>How bad is it?</i>

8
00:00:18.880 --> 00:00:20.523
<i>Her doctor says
the next 48 hours are critical.</i>

9
00:00:20.606 --> 00:00:23.851
<i>You are my family.
so you need to wake up.</i>

10
00:00:23.989 --> 00:00:26.992
<i>You remember Juice's
defense attorney. James Ulster.</i>

11
00:00:27.441 --> 00:00:29.201
Are you my father?

12
00:00:29.339 --> 00:00:32.052
What kind of a father would
throw his own son into the garbage?

13
00:00:32.135 --> 00:00:34.586
James Ulster. I'm arresting you
for the murders

14
00:00:34.724 --> 00:00:38.348
of Donna Mary Halston
and my mother. Lucy Morales.

15
00:00:38.486 --> 00:00:40.785
Sheriff Caleb Roussard.
I'm Special Agent Will Trent.

16
00:00:40.868 --> 00:00:43.250
Sheriff Caleb Roussard
is your father.

17
00:00:43.388 --> 00:00:46.632
<i>You know how I said I grew up
in a group home? Will was there.</i>

18
00:00:46.770 --> 00:00:49.428
-Will. I'm pregnant.
-You're gonna be a mom. Ang.

19
00:00:49.566 --> 00:00:51.420
-A great one.
-Thanks for being here.

20
00:00:51.637 --> 00:00:53.777
-Of course.
-Angie? Hey.

21
00:00:53.915 --> 00:00:55.296
-She's okay.
-Okay.

22
00:00:55.434 --> 00:00:57.540
<i>-And you're okay?
-I'm okay.</i>

23
00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:05.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

24
00:01:29.503 --> 00:01:30.607
<i>How are you doing?</i>

25
00:01:30.745 --> 00:01:33.714
Great. I am great.

26
00:01:33.852 --> 00:01:35.543
Great. That's great.

27
00:01:36.026 --> 00:01:37.200
Yes.

28
00:01:40.514 --> 00:01:42.605
-Can I ask you a question. Dr. Roach?
-Yes.

29
00:01:42.688 --> 00:01:44.331
What does pickleball
have to do with therapy?

30
00:01:44.414 --> 00:01:45.850
Can't we just do this in a nice.

31
00:01:45.933 --> 00:01:47.728
air-conditioned office
like always?

32
00:01:47.866 --> 00:01:50.199
Well. we're keeping your body
busy so your brain is focused

33
00:01:50.282 --> 00:01:53.423
on returning the shot rather
than repressing your feelings.

34
00:01:53.803 --> 00:01:56.654
Won't work. I can repress my
feelings under any circumstances.

35
00:01:56.737 --> 00:01:57.772
How's Angie?

36
00:02:01.742 --> 00:02:03.986
-Still pregnant.
-How do you feel about that?

37
00:02:06.609 --> 00:02:08.611
-A little lost.
-Keep talking.

38
00:02:10.440 --> 00:02:13.063
We've only had each other
for our entire lives.

39
00:02:13.202 --> 00:02:19.000
Now she's moved on to a very
successful. emotionally secure doctor.

40
00:02:19.139 --> 00:02:20.899
and I couldn't be happier
about it.

41
00:02:21.555 --> 00:02:23.177
-Really?
-Yes.

42
00:02:23.315 --> 00:02:26.387
Because it would be
perfectly understandable

43
00:02:26.525 --> 00:02:28.651
for you to have
some mixed feelings about that.

44
00:02:28.734 --> 00:02:32.013
-I do not.
-I mean. if you weren't so scared...

45
00:02:33.049 --> 00:02:36.363
I'm fine! I said I'm fine!
I'm so fine that I'm great!

46
00:02:36.949 --> 00:02:38.296
Nice.

47
00:02:39.607 --> 00:02:42.162
I apologize
for losing my temper.

48
00:02:42.300 --> 00:02:45.372
Don't apologize. Keep it
coming. I'm not scared of you.

49
00:02:45.510 --> 00:02:49.307
I've seen the damage a man's
temper can do in this world.

50
00:02:49.445 --> 00:02:51.481
and I really try
not to go there.

51
00:02:51.930 --> 00:02:53.504
Should we ask the pickleball
how you're doing with that

52
00:02:53.587 --> 00:02:55.148
'cause it's all the way
in Macon?

53
00:02:55.692 --> 00:02:58.912
It's normal for a lot of emotion to
come up when you start therapy.

54
00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:03.286
We talked a lot about your
childhood and the abuse you suffered.

55
00:03:05.115 --> 00:03:08.153
Anger is
an appropriate response.

56
00:03:08.291 --> 00:03:09.416
but it doesn't like
to be ignored.

57
00:03:09.499 --> 00:03:12.847
So if you're mad. be mad.

58
00:03:12.985 --> 00:03:14.918
Can we please
just change the subject?

59
00:03:15.505 --> 00:03:16.679
All right.

60
00:03:16.817 --> 00:03:18.715
So. you're going
to Caleb's tonight?

61
00:03:19.164 --> 00:03:21.787
Yeah. I don't know.

62
00:03:23.030 --> 00:03:25.412
His family is loud.

63
00:03:25.550 --> 00:03:26.951
Yeah. some families are loud.

64
00:03:27.034 --> 00:03:28.898
Yeah. and they over salt
their food.

65
00:03:29.036 --> 00:03:32.315
-Not the sodium.
-Yeah. and they have an enormous dog.

66
00:03:32.453 --> 00:03:34.593
It's a Great Dane.
It's like a small horse.

67
00:03:34.731 --> 00:03:36.478
I mean. why does anybody
need a dog that big?

68
00:03:36.561 --> 00:03:38.148
What are they compensating for?

69
00:03:40.150 --> 00:03:42.553
Maybe you're looking for
reasons for this not to work

70
00:03:42.636 --> 00:03:45.190
because you don't feel worthy
of a family.

71
00:03:45.639 --> 00:03:48.029
You make me out to be
a rather sad man. Dr. Roach.

72
00:03:48.124 --> 00:03:51.714
I'm just saying you have been
surviving on crumbs

73
00:03:51.852 --> 00:03:54.820
and now you have the whole cake.

74
00:03:55.890 --> 00:03:59.963
Yes. but it is a carrot cake
with raisins.

75
00:04:07.764 --> 00:04:10.733
<i>♪ Isn't it rich ♪</i>

76
00:04:14.426 --> 00:04:17.947
<i>♪ Are we a pair ♪</i>

77
00:04:20.639 --> 00:04:22.745
And then he comes into
the living room

78
00:04:22.883 --> 00:04:25.955
while I'm hanging out with a
friend. and he goes... "New rule.

79
00:04:26.093 --> 00:04:28.426
the soy sauce no longer
needs to be refrigerated.

80
00:04:28.509 --> 00:04:30.511
From now on.
it resides in the pantry."

81
00:04:30.649 --> 00:04:32.237
In the pantry?

82
00:04:32.375 --> 00:04:34.239
I know.

83
00:04:34.377 --> 00:04:37.694
And I'm like. "Okay. do we need to
have a meeting about the ketchup?"

84
00:04:39.106 --> 00:04:41.936
The man has rules for
his kitchen. I respect that.

85
00:04:42.074 --> 00:04:44.836
This is the best chicken
I've ever had. Mrs. Roussard.

86
00:04:44.974 --> 00:04:47.563
Aw. Nico.
you're welcome back anytime.

87
00:04:47.701 --> 00:04:49.427
Here. Have some more.

88
00:04:49.875 --> 00:04:51.877
Pass me the salt.

89
00:04:52.015 --> 00:04:55.467
Do you know sharks don't have
any bones? They only have cartilage.

90
00:04:56.537 --> 00:04:58.367
Really?

91
00:04:58.505 --> 00:05:00.734
Did you know shark's eyeballs
are as big as five human eyeballs?

92
00:05:00.817 --> 00:05:03.944
You know. I was just thinking this morning
I don't know anything about sharks.

93
00:05:04.027 --> 00:05:07.734
How about we go look at your book and
you can bring me up to speed on sharks?

94
00:05:08.238 --> 00:05:09.447
Okay.

95
00:05:10.275 --> 00:05:12.173
Pass me the green beans. please.

96
00:05:13.036 --> 00:05:17.593
Now. Reed.
beluga caviar is the best.

97
00:05:17.731 --> 00:05:21.113
However. uh. it has been banned
in the United States

98
00:05:21.251 --> 00:05:25.566
due to the endangered status
of the beluga sturgeon.

99
00:05:25.704 --> 00:05:27.361
Mmm.

100
00:05:29.190 --> 00:05:31.351
-I like those black truffles we did last time.
-Oh. yes.

101
00:05:31.434 --> 00:05:35.680
Our little. uh. foodie club has
been a highlight of my prison journey.

102
00:05:35.818 --> 00:05:37.525
We sure those fish eggs
travel okay?

103
00:05:37.647 --> 00:05:39.546
Oh. yes. Yes.
<i>Lights out. everyone.</i>

104
00:05:39.684 --> 00:05:43.481
Okay. Reed. Now. normally
I serve this on a blini.

105
00:05:43.619 --> 00:05:46.035
-which is like a little crepe.
-What's a crepe?

106
00:05:46.173 --> 00:05:49.487
It's like a little pancake.
Mmm.

107
00:05:49.625 --> 00:05:56.045
But today we must improvise.
so we are using potato chips.

108
00:05:56.183 --> 00:05:58.254
Now. close your eyes. Yeah.

109
00:05:59.600 --> 00:06:01.464
All right. Ah.

110
00:06:01.602 --> 00:06:05.917
Now...
Now feel the texture. mmm?

111
00:06:06.055 --> 00:06:07.056
Mmm.

112
00:06:07.712 --> 00:06:10.680
It's like little fishy
boba bubbles only smaller.

113
00:06:10.818 --> 00:06:14.063
Fair. Fair.

114
00:06:14.201 --> 00:06:18.930
Okay. don't worry. Jerry.
I haven't forgotten about you.

115
00:06:19.068 --> 00:06:22.727
I'm going to make you
the perfect bite.

116
00:06:22.865 --> 00:06:24.867
Oh. Mmm.

117
00:06:25.454 --> 00:06:26.662
Mmm.

118
00:06:30.873 --> 00:06:32.688
Health care in this country
is so messed up.

119
00:06:32.771 --> 00:06:34.034
Why won't this damn TV come on?

120
00:06:34.117 --> 00:06:35.829
Hey. Franklin.
you need to calm down.

121
00:06:35.912 --> 00:06:37.776
Ormewood is fighting
for his life here.

122
00:06:37.914 --> 00:06:39.502
Running out of time. Franklin.

123
00:06:39.640 --> 00:06:41.435
These could be
his final moments.

124
00:06:41.573 --> 00:06:43.437
Ooh. it came.

125
00:06:43.575 --> 00:06:46.475
You look so stupid.
I really can't get over it.

126
00:06:46.613 --> 00:06:48.684
It's for Cooper.
so I don't look sick.

127
00:06:48.822 --> 00:06:50.824
It's working.
Still got his eyelashes.

128
00:06:50.962 --> 00:06:53.620
- Mmm. Okay
- Come on. man.

129
00:06:55.622 --> 00:06:57.382
-Oh!
-Oh! There it is.

130
00:06:59.488 --> 00:07:00.937
It's in Spanish?

131
00:07:01.731 --> 00:07:04.147
Ormewood. this isn't Spanish.

132
00:07:04.285 --> 00:07:05.666
You don't understand this?

133
00:07:05.804 --> 00:07:08.531
Did they leave a little tumor
in there still?

134
00:07:08.669 --> 00:07:10.464
I left a little tumor
in your mom.

135
00:07:12.673 --> 00:07:15.020
Okay. close your eyes.

136
00:07:17.367 --> 00:07:18.403
Ah.

137
00:07:18.783 --> 00:07:22.096
Ah. Now describe
what you taste.

138
00:07:22.234 --> 00:07:25.755
It's kind of subtle.
but it's also rich.

139
00:07:26.894 --> 00:07:28.758
I might even use
the word buttery.

140
00:07:29.759 --> 00:07:32.382
I actually like the taste
of the potato chip.

141
00:07:32.521 --> 00:07:37.318
The brightness of the salt really
helps the entire experience. Mmm.

142
00:07:45.568 --> 00:07:46.776
Hey!

143
00:08:03.448 --> 00:08:05.623
<i>♪ Isn't it rich ♪</i>

144
00:08:07.935 --> 00:08:09.799
<i>♪ Isn't it queer ♪</i>

145
00:08:15.391 --> 00:08:17.738
It's too late to turn back now.
my boy.

146
00:08:18.152 --> 00:08:20.465
<i>♪ And where are the clowns ♪</i>

147
00:08:20.603 --> 00:08:22.536
I love this green.

148
00:08:22.674 --> 00:08:25.991
I mean. look at it. It's fresh. It's
welcoming. It feels like spring.

149
00:08:26.126 --> 00:08:29.819
I mean. it's... it's...

150
00:08:29.957 --> 00:08:32.339
You know. it's...
it's jubilant.

151
00:08:33.029 --> 00:08:34.272
-Jubilant.
-Yeah.

152
00:08:34.410 --> 00:08:35.998
Show me the orange one. bigger.

153
00:08:37.309 --> 00:08:39.484
Okay. bossy.

154
00:08:42.176 --> 00:08:43.212
Uncle Will.

155
00:08:44.109 --> 00:08:45.594
Yes. Calvin?

156
00:08:45.732 --> 00:08:47.927
Don't tell anybody. but
sometimes when I'm in the bathtub.

157
00:08:48.010 --> 00:08:50.426
I get scared a shark
is gonna get me.

158
00:08:51.634 --> 00:08:56.950
Calvin. I promise you. sharks
cannot get you on dry land. okay?

159
00:09:00.505 --> 00:09:03.853
<i>♪ Maybe next year
They'll be here ♪</i>

160
00:09:07.650 --> 00:09:12.724
<i>♪ Maybe next year
They'll be here ♪</i>

161
00:09:14.899 --> 00:09:18.074
<i>♪ Send in the clowns ♪</i>

162
00:09:30.052 --> 00:09:31.384
James Ulster has
a big head start.

163
00:09:31.467 --> 00:09:33.503
What do we know
about this kid he's with?

164
00:09:33.642 --> 00:09:36.562
Reed Hobbs. Single homicide.
Only family he has is his grandmother.

165
00:09:36.645 --> 00:09:38.301
What's Caleb doing here?

166
00:09:38.439 --> 00:09:39.910
Any new information that
comes in comes straight to me

167
00:09:39.993 --> 00:09:42.789
so we can adjust the perimeter.
Okay? Go.

168
00:09:42.927 --> 00:09:44.169
What's all this?

169
00:09:44.653 --> 00:09:46.986
-I'm running point on the prison break.
-No. you're not.

170
00:09:47.069 --> 00:09:49.367
Prison's in Bradford County.
That's my jurisdiction.

171
00:09:49.450 --> 00:09:52.419
GBI wants me to lead up
the marshals and GDC.

172
00:09:52.557 --> 00:09:54.283
That's absurd.

173
00:09:54.421 --> 00:09:57.397
Will. this is a manhunt. not a
murder that needs to be solved.

174
00:09:58.943 --> 00:10:01.428
You think I don't know
what this man means to you?

175
00:10:01.911 --> 00:10:03.154
I'll find them.

176
00:10:07.330 --> 00:10:09.905
-Deputy Director Appleyard...
-Acting Deputy Director.

177
00:10:09.988 --> 00:10:12.805
Why are we taking a back seat to
the Bradford County Sheriff's Office?

178
00:10:12.888 --> 00:10:15.856
Agent Trent.
you're gonna lower your voice.

179
00:10:15.994 --> 00:10:18.272
-All due respect. but also not really.
-Will.

180
00:10:18.410 --> 00:10:20.847
I think you don't want us
involved in case this goes south

181
00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:22.491
because you don't wanna look bad

182
00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:24.437
because what you really want
is that deputy director job.

183
00:10:24.520 --> 00:10:27.247
-Will!
-I already have the job. Agent Trent.

184
00:10:27.799 --> 00:10:29.352
Temporarily.

185
00:10:30.802 --> 00:10:33.080
Giving this to Caleb
was my idea.

186
00:10:33.218 --> 00:10:34.185
Amanda.

187
00:10:34.323 --> 00:10:35.255
Should you be here?

188
00:10:35.393 --> 00:10:36.601
Probably not.

189
00:10:37.222 --> 00:10:39.949
But I came to give Bill
my opinion on this case.

190
00:10:40.087 --> 00:10:43.387
So. are you telling me you got out of
bed and hobbled over here with your cane

191
00:10:43.470 --> 00:10:44.816
to put me on the bench?

192
00:10:44.954 --> 00:10:47.439
Yes. I did.
You're too close to this. Will.

193
00:10:47.577 --> 00:10:50.428
Oh. okay. Well then. I guess. you
know. I'll just go take a bubble bath

194
00:10:50.511 --> 00:10:53.017
-and wait for James Ulster to kill somebody else.
-Okay. Let's go.

195
00:10:53.100 --> 00:10:55.171
This behavior
is proving my point!

196
00:10:55.309 --> 00:10:57.650
It's insane that you would
take me off this case.

197
00:10:57.760 --> 00:11:00.832
I know Ulster better than any
of you or Sheriff Roussard.

198
00:11:00.970 --> 00:11:03.490
This man killed my mother
and left me to die.

199
00:11:04.077 --> 00:11:07.238
So on behalf of the state of Georgia.
I would just like to say thank you both

200
00:11:07.321 --> 00:11:10.877
-for your terrible judgment.
-Oh. my God. Will. come on.

201
00:11:11.498 --> 00:11:12.430
Go.

202
00:11:14.604 --> 00:11:17.663
I consider this a complete and total
undermining of me by Amanda Wagner.

203
00:11:17.746 --> 00:11:19.941
Let the marshals do the
roadblocks and watch the busses.

204
00:11:20.024 --> 00:11:21.404
We can still investigate.

205
00:11:22.095 --> 00:11:23.717
Wait. was this always here?

206
00:11:26.271 --> 00:11:28.446
-You can't knock?
-I got a project for you.

207
00:11:28.584 --> 00:11:30.537
Ormewood. why are you in
this tiny dark closet?

208
00:11:30.620 --> 00:11:32.988
This is my office. okay? They
gave me this new computer job.

209
00:11:33.071 --> 00:11:35.025
and I can't do it
unless I have peace and quiet.

210
00:11:35.108 --> 00:11:36.730
-What do you need?
-It's Ulster.

211
00:11:36.868 --> 00:11:38.200
We need to figure out
where he's going.

212
00:11:38.283 --> 00:11:40.381
I thought you guys
got thrown off that case.

213
00:11:40.492 --> 00:11:42.515
-How'd you know that?
-It's on the WhatsApp chain.

214
00:11:42.598 --> 00:11:45.483
We're working the case on the
DL. which is why we're using you.

215
00:11:45.566 --> 00:11:47.589
We know that Ulster is
well connected and charming.

216
00:11:47.672 --> 00:11:49.626
It's possible that
he's using people to help him.

217
00:11:49.709 --> 00:11:50.696
and we want to know who.

218
00:11:50.779 --> 00:11:52.712
Morning. Snack time.

219
00:11:52.850 --> 00:11:54.801
It's not vending machine hours.
Franklin.

220
00:11:54.886 --> 00:11:57.233
You made that up. Ormy.
No such thing.

221
00:11:57.371 --> 00:12:00.650
No. you don't fit inside of
here. okay? Absolutely not.

222
00:12:00.789 --> 00:12:02.100
Discrimination.

223
00:12:02.238 --> 00:12:04.033
Will. hi.

224
00:12:04.171 --> 00:12:06.401
You think four armed officers stationed
at my place is a little excessive?

225
00:12:06.484 --> 00:12:07.865
No. I do not.

226
00:12:08.003 --> 00:12:09.438
James Ulster abducted you
from my home last time.

227
00:12:09.521 --> 00:12:11.578
so it makes perfect sense
to give you protection.

228
00:12:11.661 --> 00:12:13.822
I can also come over and sleep
on the couch if that's better for you.

229
00:12:13.905 --> 00:12:15.907
No?
Then four armed guards it is.

230
00:12:16.045 --> 00:12:17.875
So. uh.
what are we all doing in here?

231
00:12:18.392 --> 00:12:20.104
It's 'cause you got kicked
off the Ulster manhunt.

232
00:12:20.187 --> 00:12:21.588
-I saw it on the WhatsApp.
-Yeah.

233
00:12:21.671 --> 00:12:23.418
What's everyone talking about?
What is this?

234
00:12:23.501 --> 00:12:24.951
APD-GBI gossip.

235
00:12:25.089 --> 00:12:26.987
It's a group chat everyone's on.

236
00:12:27.125 --> 00:12:28.506
Oh. you're not on it?

237
00:12:29.679 --> 00:12:31.336
-Are you on it?
-Yes.

238
