00:25:24.799 --> 00:25:27.111
How about
an unwavering belief in love?

479
00:25:28.872 --> 00:25:29.804
Who are you?

480
00:25:29.942 --> 00:25:31.875
I don't know. man.

481
00:25:32.013 --> 00:25:35.416
Ever since I got sick. I've been moved
by people and their stupid feelings.

482
00:25:35.499 --> 00:25:38.523
She wanted a connection. It
was the best option she could find.

483
00:25:38.606 --> 00:25:40.090
Are you okay?

484
00:25:40.228 --> 00:25:42.667
My nauseous day is also
sometimes my emotional day.

485
00:25:42.886 --> 00:25:44.819
I probably shouldn't
have come here.

486
00:25:44.957 --> 00:25:47.393
I'm gonna close my eyes for a few
seconds. Tell me when she shows up. yeah?

487
00:25:47.476 --> 00:25:48.926
-Noted.
-Okay.

488
00:25:52.585 --> 00:25:56.244
Angela Agnes Bernadette
Polaski. are you engaged?

489
00:25:58.315 --> 00:26:00.579
Speaking of an unwavering
belief in love. let me see the ring.

490
00:26:00.662 --> 00:26:02.146
Oh!

491
00:26:02.284 --> 00:26:03.582
-Congrats. Polaski. You bagged a doctor?
-Ah!

492
00:26:03.665 --> 00:26:05.667
-Yeah.
-Ooh!

493
00:26:05.805 --> 00:26:07.413
Make sure you tell him to invite all of
his gay doctor friends to the wedding.

494
00:26:07.496 --> 00:26:08.725
Look at all these diamonds.

495
00:26:08.808 --> 00:26:10.603
I know.
it's kind of a lot. right?

496
00:26:10.741 --> 00:26:12.522
Well. like. he gave me another
one. but I kinda like this one.

497
00:26:12.605 --> 00:26:15.401
No. no. no. Hey. no. No. Do
not put that on the WhatsApp.

498
00:26:15.539 --> 00:26:18.024
-Come on. this is breaking news!
-No!

499
00:26:22.028 --> 00:26:23.685
Will doesn't know yet?

500
00:26:25.031 --> 00:26:28.069
-Not yet.
-Oh. man. He's gonna be crushed.

501
00:26:28.897 --> 00:26:30.830
-Can I tell him?
-Absolutely not.

502
00:26:30.968 --> 00:26:33.143
You feeling a little
conflicted. preggy?

503
00:26:33.281 --> 00:26:35.076
No. just...

504
00:26:36.871 --> 00:26:37.996
All right. stakeout rules apply?

505
00:26:38.079 --> 00:26:39.494
Nothing leaves this car.

506
00:26:39.632 --> 00:26:40.875
Car is sacred.

507
00:26:43.360 --> 00:26:44.430
Okay.

508
00:26:44.948 --> 00:26:47.675
God. I love Seth. He's...

509
00:26:48.607 --> 00:26:50.367
He's so good to me.

510
00:26:51.748 --> 00:26:53.211
You know. when he looks at me.

511
00:26:53.301 --> 00:26:56.925
I don't see all the mistakes
I made looking back.

512
00:26:57.477 --> 00:27:00.239
But sometimes I think
about the universe where...

513
00:27:01.896 --> 00:27:03.173
it's Will.

514
00:27:04.243 --> 00:27:07.266
I don't know what that means.
and I feel really guilty about it.

515
00:27:07.349 --> 00:27:09.739
'Cause you're beating
yourself up for being human.

516
00:27:10.939 --> 00:27:13.217
Oh. look.
there's Janice-Theresa.

517
00:27:13.355 --> 00:27:14.943
-Hey.
-Where?

518
00:27:15.841 --> 00:27:17.636
Oh. God. Look at this lady.

519
00:27:17.774 --> 00:27:22.054
Yeah. look at her. Polaski.
She's engaged to a serial killer.

520
00:27:22.192 --> 00:27:23.938
Do you think that
she's beating herself up?

521
00:27:24.021 --> 00:27:25.471
-She is not.
-Mm-mmm.

522
00:27:25.609 --> 00:27:27.597
She just goes to Kroger.
buys a low-fat cottage cheese.

523
00:27:27.680 --> 00:27:31.477
her Chardonnay and her modest
tops. And goes about her life.

524
00:27:32.754 --> 00:27:34.618
Whoa!

525
00:27:34.756 --> 00:27:36.240
Oh.

526
00:27:36.378 --> 00:27:38.608
-Uh. you just hit my mailbox!
-Oh. that was on purpose.

527
00:27:38.691 --> 00:27:41.266
-Screw that mailbox. Hey. bitch.
-Wait. do they know each other?

528
00:27:41.349 --> 00:27:42.902
-What?
-You've been lying.

529
00:27:43.040 --> 00:27:44.476
-I don't know you.
-You don't have to know me.

530
00:27:44.559 --> 00:27:46.064
-I don't know you!
-Don't you throw that at me!

531
00:27:46.147 --> 00:27:47.306
-She threw her with that.
-I don't know you!

532
00:27:47.389 --> 00:27:48.722
-You're gonna know me...
-Bread.

533
00:27:48.805 --> 00:27:50.427
...'cause you're a liar.

534
00:27:50.565 --> 00:27:52.311
-Come on. Let's go.
-No. no. Hold on. It's getting good.

535
00:27:52.394 --> 00:27:53.370
-Come on.
-Come on.

536
00:27:55.018 --> 00:27:57.158
-Oh. my God.
-Girl. she can run.

537
00:27:57.296 --> 00:27:58.884
Oh!

538
00:27:59.022 --> 00:28:00.354
Okay. I feel like
we should call it.

539
00:28:00.437 --> 00:28:02.080
Just wanna see how it play out.
Come on.

540
00:28:02.163 --> 00:28:03.785
Oh. not the car!

541
00:28:03.923 --> 00:28:07.651
You are not his fiancee! I am!

542
00:28:07.789 --> 00:28:09.170
He's mine!

543
00:28:09.308 --> 00:28:11.399
Two fiances. One serial killer.
two fiancees.

544
00:28:11.482 --> 00:28:12.794
-Get off!
-I love my job.

545
00:28:12.932 --> 00:28:14.244
Oh!

546
00:28:14.382 --> 00:28:16.246
-No.
-No. wait. wait.

547
00:28:16.384 --> 00:28:18.386
You get off!
I don't know you.

548
00:28:18.524 --> 00:28:19.801
Nice reversal!

549
00:28:19.939 --> 00:28:21.630
Hmm. way to come back.
All right.

550
00:28:21.769 --> 00:28:23.322
No. You!

551
00:28:23.460 --> 00:28:24.806
Um... All right.

552
00:28:24.944 --> 00:28:26.505
She got that slam. look at that.

553
00:28:26.705 --> 00:28:28.051
Get off me!

554
00:28:28.534 --> 00:28:32.055
-Uh-oh.
-Yeah. APD.

555
00:28:34.954 --> 00:28:38.406
Nurses say she sleeps for 23 hours
a day. hadn't been verbal for weeks.

556
00:28:38.544 --> 00:28:40.398
They're just waiting
for her to let go.

557
00:28:40.511 --> 00:28:42.375
And she hadn't had any visitors.

558
00:28:42.997 --> 00:28:45.046
Well. someone brought her
those chocolates.

559
00:28:59.082 --> 00:29:00.324
Freeze! GBI!

560
00:29:00.842 --> 00:29:02.533
Reed Hobbs. stop!

561
00:29:16.375 --> 00:29:19.240
I can't breathe.

562
00:29:22.450 --> 00:29:23.727
Reed. stop!

563
00:29:33.633 --> 00:29:35.463
Reed. Reed.

564
00:29:35.981 --> 00:29:38.742
Listen. I just...
Okay. easy. easy.

565
00:29:38.880 --> 00:29:41.193
I just wanna talk. okay?

566
00:29:41.710 --> 00:29:44.852
-I don't wanna hurt anyone.
-I know that.

567
00:29:46.715 --> 00:29:50.340
You just wanted to see your
grandmother... one last time

568
00:29:51.444 --> 00:29:52.756
to say goodbye.

569
00:29:52.894 --> 00:29:54.102
Isn't that right?

570
00:29:55.448 --> 00:29:57.594
Look. I know what happened
at the restaurant.

571
00:29:59.073 --> 00:30:01.938
I know James Ulster
killed all those people.

572
00:30:02.076 --> 00:30:04.078
I think you wanted
no part of it.

573
00:30:05.596 --> 00:30:07.219
He loves me.

574
00:30:07.667 --> 00:30:11.361
I know he does.
But he's dangerous. okay?

575
00:30:11.499 --> 00:30:15.434
And he's gonna get you
killed. Reed. I know him.

576
00:30:15.883 --> 00:30:18.195
Let me help you. please.

577
00:30:19.541 --> 00:30:21.095
You're Will. right?

578
00:30:22.717 --> 00:30:24.823
He said you're his son too.

579
00:30:25.754 --> 00:30:26.997
Yes.

580
00:30:28.274 --> 00:30:29.640
You know what that makes us?

581
00:30:30.518 --> 00:30:33.038
-We're brothers?
-That's right.

582
00:30:34.039 --> 00:30:37.076
You can trust me. Reed. okay?

583
00:30:37.663 --> 00:30:41.356
Let's put down the gun.
Let's just talk a little. okay?

584
00:30:42.357 --> 00:30:44.187
Tell me what his plan is.

585
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:47.535
So we can stop him
from hurting anybody else.

586
00:30:49.778 --> 00:30:51.401
I don't wanna do this anymore.

587
00:30:59.754 --> 00:31:02.205
No.

588
00:31:03.931 --> 00:31:06.174
What the hell did you just do?

589
00:31:11.110 --> 00:31:13.271
-What the hell happened here?
-A lot of big feelings.

590
00:31:13.354 --> 00:31:15.238
What happened is.
he just shot our best lead.

591
00:31:15.321 --> 00:31:19.291
No. I took out an escaped murderer
that had a gun pointed at you.

592
00:31:19.429 --> 00:31:20.899
You're not even
supposed to be here. Trent.

593
00:31:20.982 --> 00:31:23.177
Thanks to Sheriff Roussard.
our job's half done.

594
00:31:23.260 --> 00:31:24.489
He had a gun pointed on you?

595
00:31:24.572 --> 00:31:26.279
He was lowering it.
We were talking.

596
00:31:26.401 --> 00:31:27.733
He could have helped us
find Ulster.

597
00:31:27.816 --> 00:31:32.373
I don't care! Okay?
You don't know that kid!

598
00:31:32.511 --> 00:31:34.292
Could've changed his mind
blowing your head off!

599
00:31:34.375 --> 00:31:36.066
-I have zero regrets!
-Really?

600
00:31:36.204 --> 00:31:38.413
You know. every life I've taken
weighs on me.

601
00:31:38.551 --> 00:31:40.691
It's so nice that
you can sleep at night.

602
00:31:40.829 --> 00:31:42.590
This isn't your case. Will!

603
00:31:43.142 --> 00:31:44.958
One of the dead guards'
credit cards pinged

604
00:31:45.041 --> 00:31:46.700
at a car rental agency
in Savannah.

605
00:31:46.835 --> 00:31:49.217
Probably Ulster.
I'm gonna go look into it.

606
00:31:49.735 --> 00:31:51.461
All right.
I'll handle the media.

607
00:31:53.256 --> 00:31:56.052
Go back to the office. Will.

608
00:32:03.024 --> 00:32:06.372
Look at him. Can't wait to get
his face in front of a camera.

609
00:32:06.510 --> 00:32:07.822
Oh!

610
00:32:07.960 --> 00:32:10.066
-Are you okay? Okay. okay.
-Yeah.

611
00:32:10.204 --> 00:32:11.377
I just need to sit.

612
00:32:11.515 --> 00:32:13.517
Okay.
All right. easy now.

613
00:32:15.243 --> 00:32:17.452
Great.
This is just what I need.

614
00:32:17.590 --> 00:32:20.593
It's Bill Appleyard watching me
collapse in the street.

615
00:32:20.731 --> 00:32:24.701
Okay. so. what are we gonna do
about this jackass?

616
00:32:25.564 --> 00:32:27.393
Should we kill him?

617
00:32:27.531 --> 00:32:31.363
Guys like that can't be killed.
They just get promoted.

618
00:32:32.812 --> 00:32:35.643
How's Will doin'? Really.

619
00:32:36.333 --> 00:32:38.094
I think
if we don't catch this guy.

620
00:32:38.232 --> 00:32:40.234
then he's gonna go off
the deep end.

621
00:32:41.235 --> 00:32:43.479
And it's not helping
that he's not on the case.

622
00:32:44.100 --> 00:32:46.965
I know.

623
00:32:48.138 --> 00:32:50.244
I just can't lose him.

624
00:32:57.458 --> 00:33:00.668
But James. he would
write me these letters.

625
00:33:00.806 --> 00:33:05.569
I mean. long. long letters that
were full of the most romantic things.

626
00:33:05.707 --> 00:33:07.054
I mean. one time...

627
00:33:07.192 --> 00:33:09.214
He told me he wished my eyes
were swimming pools so...

628
00:33:09.297 --> 00:33:13.646
So he could just. boop.
take a dip in my eyes.

629
00:33:13.784 --> 00:33:16.635
Isn't that the most romantic
thing you've ever heard? I know.

630
00:33:16.718 --> 00:33:18.775
I can see how that
would bowl a person over.

631
00:33:18.858 --> 00:33:20.881
Do you have any idea
where he might be going?

632
00:33:20.964 --> 00:33:25.003
He says his last thought before
he drifts off is the smell of my hair.

633
00:33:26.556 --> 00:33:28.199
He's never even
smelled my hair before.

634
00:33:28.282 --> 00:33:30.477
It's just the thought
of the smell of my hair.

635
00:33:30.560 --> 00:33:32.596
It just holds him in a spell.

636
00:33:32.734 --> 00:33:35.806
He has killed ten people
in the last 48 hours.

637
00:33:35.944 --> 00:33:37.463
Aw. I hope he's okay.

638
00:33:37.601 --> 00:33:39.362
I'm sure he had his reasons.

639
00:33:39.500 --> 00:33:42.468
We know that a courier made
a drop of cash and passports.

640
00:33:42.606 --> 00:33:44.608
Was that you or was that Lisa?

641
00:33:44.746 --> 00:33:48.612
You really think that piece of
trash could come up with ten grand?

642
00:33:48.750 --> 00:33:49.806
Okay. so that was you.

643
00:33:49.889 --> 00:33:52.513
I didn't say that.
Did I say that?

644
00:33:52.651 --> 00:33:54.342
Okay.

645
00:33:54.480 --> 00:33:56.537
I've had enough. You wanna hear
what your fiance has been telling Lisa?

646
00:33:56.620 --> 00:33:58.588
<i>He says his last thought</i>

647
00:33:58.726 --> 00:34:01.453
<i>before he drifts off
is the smell of my hair.</i>

648
00:34:01.591 --> 00:34:02.626
But...

649
00:34:03.455 --> 00:34:07.562
But that was our thing.
That was our thing.

650
00:34:07.700 --> 00:34:10.117
<i>It's just the thought
of the smell of my hair.</i>

651
00:34:10.255 --> 00:34:11.739
<i>It just holds him in a spell.</i>

652
00:34:11.877 --> 00:34:13.154
Oh. that two-timing...

653
00:34:13.292 --> 00:34:15.260
Asshole.

654
00:34:16.640 --> 00:34:20.265
I love him.
but that was my thing.

655
00:34:20.403 --> 00:34:23.164
He's never even
smelled her hair.

656
00:34:23.302 --> 00:34:26.202
Well. ours is pissed
and she lawyered up.

657
00:34:26.340 --> 00:34:28.514
Mine's uncontrollably weeping.

658
00:34:29.998 --> 00:34:31.414
Let me take a run at weepy.

659
00:34:31.552 --> 00:34:34.072
-What are you gonna do?
-Don't worry about it.

660
00:34:35.866 --> 00:34:39.180
Thank you.

661
00:34:44.979 --> 00:34:48.189
October 14th. 2017.

662
00:34:48.327 --> 00:34:49.604
What?

663
00:34:49.742 --> 00:34:53.021
It was a Saturday.
Ruth's Chris Steak House.

664
00:34:53.781 --> 00:34:55.679
I was waiting on
my boyfriend. Jerod.

665
00:34:55.817 --> 00:35:00.063
We were eight months in.
and I was in love.

666
00:35:00.201 --> 00:35:01.616
<i>♪ I grew strong ♪</i>

667
00:35:01.754 --> 00:35:03.811
But then my buddy Charles
texted me a bombshell

668
00:35:03.894 --> 00:35:08.934
that Jerod was married
to a woman with two kids.

669
00:35:09.072 --> 00:35:10.763
-In Marietta.
-Really?

670
00:35:11.212 --> 00:35:12.144
Men are pigs.

671
00:35:12.282 --> 00:35:13.594
I know.

672
00:35:13.732 --> 00:35:15.906
So I see you. Janice-Theresa.

673
00:35:16.044 --> 00:35:19.634
and I want you to know
that you are not alone.

674
00:35:19.772 --> 00:35:22.016
We're all Janice-Theresa Weggle.

675
00:35:22.154 --> 00:35:24.867
So let me tell you something as
one Janice-Theresa to another.

676
00:35:24.950 --> 00:35:28.056
This is not
the end of your story.

677
00:35:28.195 --> 00:35:29.644
Yeah. it is.

678
00:35:29.782 --> 00:35:32.992
This is where your story begins.

679
00:35:33.131 --> 00:35:37.031
No. It is not. I don't think
I'll ever love again.

680
00:35:37.169 --> 00:35:38.205
<i>♪ No. not I ♪</i>

681
00:35:38.343 --> 00:35:41.518
Yes. you will.

682
00:35:41.656 --> 00:35:43.417
You're gonna come back
from this.

683
00:35:43.555 --> 00:35:45.798
You're gonna rise
from the ashes.

684
00:35:45.936 --> 00:35:49.319
In fact. I'm gonna call you
Janice-Theresa-Phoenix.

685
00:35:49.457 --> 00:35:52.288
Oh. I don't know.
That's a lot of hyphens.

686
00:35:52.426 --> 00:35:56.740
You are worth it. Janice
hyphen Theresa hyphen Phoenix.

687
00:35:56.878 --> 00:35:59.433
She's eating out of
the palm of his hand.

688
00:36:00.744 --> 00:36:03.299
-Is this story true?
-Who cares?

689
00:36:05.818 --> 00:36:07.648
Hey. Now look.
there's only one thing

690
00:36:07.786 --> 00:36:11.962
standing between you and the
sweet revenge of a happy life.

691
00:36:12.100 --> 00:36:14.206
-What?
-You're in a bit of trouble now.

692
00:36:14.344 --> 00:36:17.796
-No.
-You have aided and abetted a known felon

693
00:36:17.934 --> 00:36:19.970
who is racking up
quite a body count.

694
00:36:20.108 --> 00:36:21.524
Are they gonna...

695
00:36:21.662 --> 00:36:23.167
Are they gonna
give me the chair?

696
00:36:23.250 --> 00:36:25.134
We're gonna do everything
in our power to avoid that.

697
00:36:25.217 --> 00:36:27.274
but I need you to be honest
with me so I can save your life.

698
00:36:27.357 --> 00:36:28.600
Yeah. yeah.

699
00:36:28.738 --> 00:36:31.361
Now. Ulster's had.
like. two fiancees.

700
00:36:31.499 --> 00:36:34.157
Is it possible that
maybe there's a third?

701
00:36:34.295 --> 00:36:35.986
-Maybe even a fourth?
-No. No!

702
00:36:36.124 --> 00:36:39.266
No. it's not possible.
It's just... It's...

703
00:36:39.404 --> 00:36:41.302
Well. there was Jackie.

704
00:36:41.854 --> 00:36:44.409
but they ended things
about a year ago. so...

705
00:36:45.237 --> 00:36:46.721
Who's Jackie?

706
00:36:47.826 --> 00:36:49.276
My sister.

707
00:36:49.724 --> 00:36:52.071
I'm gonna need an address. JTP.

708
00:36:52.210 --> 00:36:54.315
<i>♪ I will survive ♪</i>

709
00:37:07.190 --> 00:37:10.400
Jackie Weggle. Two
gunshot wounds to the chest.

710
00:37:10.538 --> 00:37:12.713
Pete thinks it was less
than two hours ago.

711
00:37:15.302 --> 00:37:16.544
Why would he do this?

712
00:37:16.682 --> 00:37:19.340
Well. her car is missing. so...

713
00:37:21.308 --> 00:37:23.965
You're not acting like
you got kicked off the case.

714
00:37:24.103 --> 00:37:27.831
Yeah. well... I had to see.

715
00:37:28.729 --> 00:37:30.972
Now he's killing the women
who helped him.

716
00:37:32.284 --> 00:37:34.217
He's never gonna stop.

717
00:37:34.355 --> 00:37:36.564
Will. you can sit this out.

718
00:37:37.013 --> 00:37:39.084
We got this.
You didn't create this guy.

719
00:37:39.222 --> 00:37:40.430
No.

720
00:37:42.329 --> 00:37:43.985
But he created me.

721
00:37:46.022 --> 00:37:48.680
He put me in that trash can.
He...

722
00:37:49.543 --> 00:37:54.513
This man dictated my whole life
from the moment I was born.

723
00:37:59.415 --> 00:38:00.968
I have to end this.

724
00:38:01.624 --> 00:38:03.453
So you're torturing yourself.

725
00:38:04.868 --> 00:38:05.904
A little bit.

726
00:38:07.906 --> 00:38:12.324
He's. uh... He's in my head.

727
00:38:13.601 --> 00:38:15.465
Oh.

728
00:38:16.880 --> 00:38:18.917
He beating the crap
out of you in there?

729
00:38:23.266 --> 00:38:24.474
Yeah.

730
00:38:37.729 --> 00:38:40.801
By the way. congratulations.

731
00:38:41.249 --> 00:38:42.285
What?

732
00:38:42.423 --> 00:38:44.356
I saw the ring.

733
00:38:45.599 --> 00:38:47.117
Happy for you. Ang.

734
00:39:01.822 --> 00:39:04.259
We have full surveillance
on the rental car agency.

735
00:39:04.342 --> 00:39:06.171
Ulster hasn't shown up.

736
00:39:06.309 --> 00:39:08.780
We have flock cameras checking
for Jackie Weggle's Chevy Malibu.

737
00:39:08.863 --> 00:39:10.610
We think that's
what he's driving now.

738
00:39:10.693 --> 00:39:12.626
I have all my men
watching the agency.

739
00:39:12.764 --> 00:39:15.456
and the moment James Ulster
shows up. we'll have him.

740
00:39:18.252 --> 00:39:21.497
<i>Unknown number calling.</i>

741
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:24.120
<i>Unknown number calling.</i>

742
00:39:25.397 --> 00:39:27.192
Trent.

743
00:39:27.330 --> 00:39:30.782
Did you know sharks can hear
their prey from 3.000 feet away?

744
00:39:33.509 --> 00:39:35.200
What did you do?

745
00:39:35.338 --> 00:39:39.100
Nothing yet. but if I have
to hear another shark fact...

746
00:39:39.238 --> 00:39:40.999
<i>If you hurt that boy. James...</i>

747
00:39:41.137 --> 00:39:43.450
<i>No. Will. you are not
in charge this time.</i>

748
00:39:43.588 --> 00:39:44.934
I am.

749
00:39:46.211 --> 00:39:47.868
He took my son.

750
00:39:49.732 --> 00:39:51.147
<i>I'm taking his.</i>

751
00:39:54.426 --> 00:39:56.083
Tell me where to meet you.

752
00:39:58.741 --> 00:40:02.227
<i>♪ Mystic palm
Gem and tarot ♪</i>

753
00:40:02.365 --> 00:40:03.331
Hello. Will.

754
00:40:03.470 --> 00:40:05.057
You can stop right there.

755
00:40:05.851 --> 00:40:08.129
Uncle Will.
we've been waiting for you.

756
00:40:11.995 --> 00:40:15.205
You can put yours...
right here.

757
00:40:16.690 --> 00:40:19.175
Hey. Calvin.
I got a new one for you.

758
00:40:20.728 --> 00:40:24.732
Did you know that sharks can't
get cavities? Isn't that crazy?

759
00:40:24.870 --> 00:40:28.633
Lucky sharks. No dentist.

760
00:40:29.461 --> 00:40:32.395
Hey. you see that family
over there?

761
00:40:32.982 --> 00:40:34.625
I want you to run over to them.
all right?

762
00:40:34.708 --> 00:40:36.675
You're gonna ask
to use their cell phone.

763
00:40:36.813 --> 00:40:40.334
Call this number. ask to speak
to Faith Mitchell. She's my friend.

764
00:40:40.472 --> 00:40:42.612
You tell her you need
to be picked up. okay?

765
00:40:42.750 --> 00:40:44.580
Okay. What are you doing?

766
00:40:44.718 --> 00:40:48.515
I'm gonna hang here and play a
little game with my friend James.

767
00:40:49.101 --> 00:40:52.242
Go ahead. okay?
Your mom's gonna be worried.

768
00:40:54.210 --> 00:40:55.556
Well. I'm gonna miss you.

769
00:40:58.525 --> 00:40:59.974
Bye-bye.

770
00:41:01.976 --> 00:41:03.806
Oh. I knew you'd come.

771
00:41:04.600 --> 00:41:06.256
Because deep down...

772
00:41:06.878 --> 00:41:10.709
you know I'm the father
you deserve.

773
00:41:12.711 --> 00:41:14.023
Maybe.

774
00:41:14.161 --> 00:41:18.234
The problem is...
I'm running out of options.

775
00:41:19.477 --> 00:41:22.687
Caleb. cliche though he may be.

776
00:41:22.825 --> 00:41:24.999
is surprisingly good at his job.

777
00:41:35.320 --> 00:41:39.186
You and your cowboy father
will never stop looking for me.

778
00:41:39.324 --> 00:41:43.086
which leaves me
with just one choice.

779
00:41:44.363 --> 00:41:45.917
And what's that?

780
00:41:51.888 --> 00:41:54.235
It's time to die.

781
00:41:56.893 --> 00:41:59.827
<i>♪ Our mother's milk
Double faro ♪</i>

782
00:41:59.965 --> 00:42:01.415
You ready?

783
00:42:01.553 --> 00:42:03.762
All right. Let's go.

784
00:42:04.694 --> 00:42:07.110
It's good to see your family.

785
00:42:08.802 --> 00:42:10.873
-Calvin. you okay?
-Yeah. he's okay.

786
00:42:11.011 --> 00:42:13.102
We got to turn on the
police sirens. right. Calvin?

787
00:42:13.185 --> 00:42:14.290
Come here. baby.

788
00:42:15.015 --> 00:42:17.210
-What happened?
-Ulster took him from his day camp

789
00:42:17.293 --> 00:42:22.367
and then. according to Calvin.
Uncle Will traded places with him.

790
00:42:22.747 --> 00:42:23.955
Ulster has Will?

791
00:42:26.544 --> 00:42:27.752
Roussard.

792
00:42:30.720 --> 00:42:32.066
They found the Malibu.

793
00:42:32.204 --> 00:42:33.274
What?

794
00:42:50.602 --> 00:42:53.985
They found two bodies.
Is it Will's?

795
00:42:58.714 --> 00:43:01.026
It's not. is it?

796
00:43:02.096 --> 00:43:03.270
It's his.

797
00:43:03.408 --> 00:43:04.789
Oh. my God.

798
00:43:06.514 --> 00:43:07.964
Will.

798
